title: Live From Rotterdam: Semi-Final One
text:
Live From Rotterdam: Semi-Final One
The Grand Final of the 65th Eurovision Song Contest will take place on May 22 at Rotterdam Ahoy in Rotterdam, the Netherlands. 39 artists will take to the stage over three nights to perform their contributions for the contest, fighting to become the winner of the Eurovision Song Contest 2021.
This evening is the jury show for Semi-Final One, in which 50% of the results for tomorrow’s show will be decided. Juries in the sixteen nations taking to the stage, as well as those in Germany, Italy and the Netherlands, will be voting on the performances.
The running order for the performances are as follows:
Lithuania: The Roop – “Discoteque” Slovenia: Ana Soklič – “Amen” Russia: Manizha – “Russian Woman” Sweden: Tusse – “Million Voices” Australia: Montaigne – “Technicolour” North Macedonia: Vasil – “Here I Stand” Ireland: Lesley Roy – “Maps” Cyprus: Elena Tsagrinou – “El diablo” Norway: Tix – “Fallen Angel” Croatia: Albina – “Tick Tock” Belgium: Hooverphonic – “The Wrong Place” Israel: Eden Alene – “Set Me Free” Romania: Roxen – “Amnesia” Azerbaijan: Efendi – “Mata Hari” Ukraine: Go_A – “Shum” Malta: Destiny – “Je me casse”
LIVE COVERAGE | Live Blog In Progress
20:52 CET // Live coverage of the first dress rehearsal for Semi-Final One of the Eurovision Song Contest 2021 will commence soon.
20:58 CET // Goedenavond iedereen and welcome to the jury show of semi-final 1 of the Eurovision Song Contest 2021!
21:00 CET // The opening montage shows the LED house from the postacrds in locations around the Netherlands.
21:01 CET // The 3,500 strong audience goes wild!
21:02 CET // Duncan Laurence, the reigning Eurovision champion, opens the show with “Feel Something”.
21:04 CET // After a small dance performance and fireworks, our hosts Edisilia, Chantal, Jan and Nikkie enter the stage.
21:06 CET // The hosts are now explaining the voting procedure.
Lithuania: The Roop – “Discoteque”
21:08 CET // The Roop’s postcard was filmed at Rotterdam Central Station.
